<li>Human Rights Day (December 10)</li>
<li>Hanukkah (changes annually)</li>
<li>Kwanzaa (December 26 &#8211; January 1)</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>January
<ul>
<li>National Braille Literacy Month</li>
<li>Martin Luther King Jr. Day (January 15)</li>
<li>National Religious Freedom Day (January 16)</li>
<li>International Day of Acceptance (January 20)</li>
