		<item>
		<title>8 Ways to Master Green Marketing (+5 Eco-Friendly Brands to Follow)</title>
		<link>https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/04/28/green-marketing</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Lisa Smith]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 28 Apr 2022 15:29:01 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Diversity & Inclusion]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.wordstream.com/?p=60656</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Save the planet and attract customers with these tips and examples from truly green brands.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/04/28/green-marketing">8 Ways to Master Green Marketing (+5 Eco-Friendly Brands to Follow)</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Just last week, we celebrated the 52nd anniversary of Earth Day, which helped give rise to the environmental movement more than half a century ago.</p>
<p>Now, of course, it‚Äôs far more common to see brands prioritize the environment than it was in 1970.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-infographic.jpg" alt="green marketing infographic" width="447" height="650" class="aligncenter wp-image-60678" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://blog.gwi.com/chart-of-the-week/lifting-the-lid-on-sustainable-packaging/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Image source</a></em></p>
<p>And this, of course, spurred the rise of green marketing. What exactly does that mean? Read on to learn:</p>
<ul>
<li>What green (or sustainable) marketing is and why it&#8217;s important</li>
<li>Five of the most eco-friendly brands to give you inspiration</li>
<li>Eight ways to implement your own green marketing</li>
</ul>
<h2>What is green marketing?</h2>
<p>Sustainability marketing, or green marketing, is a practice that emphasizes the environmental benefits of a product or service, which also reflects a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/06/09/company-core-values">brand‚Äôs values.</a></p>
<p>‚ÄúOverall, the objective is to advocate toward an end mission,‚Äù said digital marketing specialist <a href="https://matttutt.me/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Matt Tutt</a>, who focuses on ethical, green, and sustainable businesses. ‚ÄúFor example, it might be to reduce the use of fossil fuels or to pivot toward greener sources of energy.‚Äù</p>
<p>That means sustainability marketing is a big shift from traditional marketing, which focuses on revenue and profits.</p>
<p>But the definition of sustainability is shifting. <a href="https://shelhorowitz.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shel Horowitz</a>, a green business profitability expert, noted that ultimately, brands should strive to move beyond sustainability to ‚Äúregenerativity,‚Äù which he defined as taking steps to actively make the world better, such as ‚Äúdeveloping and marketing products and services that [target] hunger, poverty, racism, other kinds of othering, catastrophic climate change and even peace.‚Äù</p>
<p>In fact, one study shows that <a href="https://co-nxt.com/blog/new-consumer-research-food-and-sustainability-post-pandemic-shifts/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">nearly half</a> of consumers now consider the definition of sustainability to include social and economic factors.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-stats-sustainability-definition.png" alt="sustainability marketing definition" width="720" height="510" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60710" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-stats-sustainability-definition.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-stats-sustainability-definition-480x340.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /><a href="https://co-nxt.com/blog/new-consumer-research-food-and-sustainability-post-pandemic-shifts/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em></em></a></p>
<h2>Why is green marketing important?</h2>
<p>Aside from the environmental benefits, sustainability marketing is important because it helps brands connect to increasingly environmentally and socially conscious consumers, said Roger Huang, head of growth operations at talent development platform <a href="http://springboard.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Springboard</a>.</p>
<p>‚ÄúSustainability is a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/01/13/digital-marketing-trends-2022">vast 2022 macro trend</a> and marketing plays an important role,‚Äù added Matt Lally, founder of the consultancy <a href="https://mattyads.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MattyAds</a>. ‚ÄúSustainability is high on the customer&#8217;s internal value system, which they embrace with higher brand loyalty and less price sensitivity.‚Äù</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/eco-friendly-brands-survey-on-consumers-sustainability.png" alt="chart showing importance of eco-friendliness to consumers" width="720" height="484" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60667" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/eco-friendly-brands-survey-on-consumers-sustainability.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/eco-friendly-brands-survey-on-consumers-sustainability-480x323.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.weforum.org/agenda/2022/03/generation-z-sustainability-lifestyle-buying-decisions/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Image source</em></a></p>
<p>This isn&#8217;t just an opinion. Studies like the one above show that consumers in every generation consider sustainability a more important factor than the brand name of a product when making a purchase. Furthermore, Facebook found that posts containing sustainability-related hashtags received <a href="https://www.facebook.com/business/news/insights/sustainability-trends-shape-consumers-decisions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">4.2x</a> more interactions per post than other posts made by CPG brands, and 10.8x more engagement for posts with eco-friendly-related <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/05/29/instagram-hashtags">hashtags</a>.<a href="https://co-nxt.com/blog/new-consumer-research-food-and-sustainability-post-pandemic-shifts/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em></em></a></p>
<h2>5 of the most eco-friendly brands to inspire you</h2>
<p>While there are many brand examples by now, a few stand out in their<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/02/22/cause-based-marketing"> cause-based marketing</a>:</p>
<h3>The Body Shop</h3>
<p>Scott McKinney, head of marketing at financial literacy site <a href="https://www.debtbombshell.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Debt Bombshell</a>, pointed to cosmetics retailer The Body Shop, which <a href="https://www.thebodyshop.com/en-au/about-us/activism/faat/a/a00018" target="_blank" rel="noopener">has been advocating for the end of animal testing since 1989</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/sustainability-marketing-body-shop-animal-testing.png" alt="sustainable brands - the body shop against animal testing" width="600" height="663" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60658" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/sustainability-marketing-body-shop-animal-testing.png 600w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/sustainability-marketing-body-shop-animal-testing-480x530.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Zaeem Chaudhary, architectural draftsman at engineering firm <a href="https://acdesignsolutions.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AC Design Solutions</a>, agreed, noting <a href="https://www.thebodyshop.com/en-us/about-us/activism/isolated-not-alone/a/a00020" target="_blank" rel="noopener">domestic violence</a> and <a href="https://www.thebodyshop.com/en-gb/about-us/activism/a/a00015" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HIV/AIDS</a> are two of many other causes the retailer has supported over the years.</p>
<h3>Ikea</h3>
<p>Meanwhile, furniture retailer Ikea <a href="https://about.ikea.com/en/sustainability/becoming-climate-positive/what-is-climate-positive" target="_blank" rel="noopener">has committed to becoming climate positive by 2030</a>. That means Ikea will not just reach net-zero carbon emissions, but it will actually be removing additional carbon dioxide from the atmosphere.</p>
<p><a href="https://about.ikea.com/en/sustainability/becoming-climate-positive/what-is-climate-positive" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/sustainability-marketing-ikea-climate-positive.png" alt="sustainability marketing - ikea" width="600" height="588" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60659" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/sustainability-marketing-ikea-climate-positive.png 600w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/sustainability-marketing-ikea-climate-positive-480x470.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw" /></a></p>
<p>‚ÄúThey have launched a ‚Äòsustainable living at home‚Äô products range after investing heavily in wind turbines and solar panels throughout the world,‚Äù Tutt said. ‚ÄúBy combining these two things, they can help to position themselves as having green energy and sustainability at the heart of their products.‚Äù</p>
<h3>Lego</h3>
<p>Likewise, toymaker Lego <a href="https://www.lego.com/en-us/sustainability/environment/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">wants to make all core products from sustainable materials by 2030</a>‚Äîand to make all packaging from renewable or recycled materials by 2025.</p>
<p>‚ÄúThis form of marketing gives the company a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/04/07/unique-selling-proposition">unique selling proposition</a> and customers are willing to walk with the company and hold it accountable until it achieves its sustainability goals,‚Äù said Doug Pierce, chief marketing adviser at analytics platform <a href="https://www.sigmacomputing.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sigma Computing</a>. ‚ÄúMoreover, customers are willing to pay more for Lego products and will continue to remain loyal to the company because of this commitment to sustainability.‚Äù</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/sustainability-marketing-lego.png" alt="sustainability marketing - legos sustainable materials page" width="720" height="362" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60660" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/sustainability-marketing-lego.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/sustainability-marketing-lego-480x241.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>The brand also has a Replay program, which <a href="https://www.lego.com/en-us/sustainability/environment/replay/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">allows customers to donate used bricks</a> to children in need. This, noted Stephen Light, CMO of retailer <a href="https://www.nolahmattress.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Nolah Mattress</a>, has the added bonus of helping to reduce waste in landfills.</p>
<p>‚ÄúWhen you consider their product is traditionally made of plastic, it‚Äôs incredibly smart to invest so much energy into the implementation of sustainable practices‚Äîthey don‚Äôt ignore the potentially negative impact their product has had, they use it to define their fight to achieve better for the planet at large,‚Äù he added. ‚ÄúThey provide goals and regular updates regarding sustainable materials and packaging, offering a level of transparency that‚Äôs crucial to strong sustainability marketing.‚Äù</p>
<h3>Patagonia</h3>
<p>Noting ‚Äúit feels like sustainability is at the heart of everything they do,‚Äù Tutt pointed to outdoor apparel brand Patagonia as another example.</p>
<p>‚ÄúThey are working hard toward building a community of people who love and care deeply for the outdoors and not simply existing to sell garments,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúTheir social feeds are full of exciting, stunning wildlife and landscapes, images and videos of people out hiking and exploring‚Äîreally putting the environment at the heart of what they do.‚Äù</p>
<p>One memorable example is the brand&#8217;s <a href="https://www.patagonia.com/stories/dont-buy-this-jacket-black-friday-and-the-new-york-times/story-18615.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Don‚Äôt Buy This Jacket campaign</a>, which brought attention to consumerism on Black Friday 2011.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.patagonia.com/stories/dont-buy-this-jacket-black-friday-and-the-new-york-times/story-18615.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/eco-friendly-brands-patagonia-dont-buy-this-jacket.jpeg" alt="eco-friendly sustainable brands - patagonia's don't buy this jacket campaign" width="652" height="1250" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60661" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/eco-friendly-brands-patagonia-dont-buy-this-jacket.jpeg 652w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/eco-friendly-brands-patagonia-dont-buy-this-jacket-480x920.jpeg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 652px, 100vw" /></a><a href="https://bettermarketing.pub/dont-buy-this-jacket-patagonia-s-daring-campaign-2b37e145046b" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Image source</em></a></p>
<p>‚ÄúPatagonia&#8217;s ethos is to build a product that will last, thus rejecting the fast fashion trends that plague our landfills,‚Äù Lally added.</p>
<h3>Starbucks</h3>
<p>Finally, coffee chain Starbucks recently announced its <a href="https://www.cnn.com/2022/03/15/business-food/starbucks-cup-sustainability/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">plans</a> to encourage more customers to drink from reusable mugs by 2025.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.cnn.com/2022/03/15/business-food/starbucks-cup-sustainability/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/most-sustainable-eco-friendly-brands-starbucks-cups.png" alt="most sustainable brands - starbucks announcement to eliminate single-use cups" width="720" height="216" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60662" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/most-sustainable-eco-friendly-brands-starbucks-cups.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/most-sustainable-eco-friendly-brands-starbucks-cups-480x144.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></a>That follows a long history of sustainable efforts.</p>
<p>‚ÄúSince the early 2000s, the company has been promoting green and humane sourcing for their products,‚Äù said Christiaan Huynen, founder of design firm <a href="https://designbro.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DesignBro</a>. ‚ÄúMoreover, the company also donates millions of dollars to other environmental programs and renewable energy developments. Starbucks also prioritizes sustainable practices in an attempt to decrease power and water waste.‚Äù</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/most-sustainable-eco-friendly-brands-starbucks-areas-of-focus.png" alt="most sustainable brands - starbucks areas of focus" width="720" height="783" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60663" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/most-sustainable-eco-friendly-brands-starbucks-areas-of-focus.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/most-sustainable-eco-friendly-brands-starbucks-areas-of-focus-480x522.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.starbucks.com/responsibility/planet/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Image source</a></em></p>
<h2>How you can implement green marketing</h2>
<p>Feeling inspired? Here are six <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/earth-day-slogans/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ways to integrate green marketing</a> into your own <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/01/18/best-marketing-strategies">marketing strategy</a>:</p>
<h3>Find the right sustainable initiative</h3>
<p>You don&#8217;t have to commit to something lofty like any of the big corporations above. ‚ÄúThis may be as simple as giving one percent of your profits to charity or as complex as devoting your business model to a specific cause,‚Äù said Joe Davies, founder of digital marketing firm <a href="https://fatjoe.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Fatjoe</a>.</p>
<p>By looking for features that can be marketed as sustainable, brands can leverage the feel-good benefit of the product or service while also providing value, he added.</p>
<h3>Keep your efforts genuine</h3>
<p>Horowitz noted that these efforts have to be genuine or you run the risk of greenwashing. Greenwashing refers to using vague and misleading tactics to appear sustainable without actually being sustainable‚Äîall in the name of benefiting the business and not the environment.<a href="http://weforum.org/agenda/2022/03/generation-z-sustainability-lifestyle-buying-decisions/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><br />
<img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-definition-greenwashing.jpg" alt="green marketing - definition of greenwashing" width="372" height="609" class="aligncenter wp-image-60668" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://blondegonerogue.com/blogs/fashion-sustainability/what-is-greenwashing" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Image source</em></a></p>
<h3>Adjust your messaging for the different levels of green</h3>
<p>‚ÄúThat&#8217;s only step one,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúStep two is reaching out to not just the Deep Green [consumers] but also the Lazy Greens and even the Non-Greens‚Äîall of whom require different marketing hooks.‚Äù</p>
<h3>Implement eco-conscious design</h3>
<p>First, consider product design‚Äîsuch as how to make your products recyclable or reusable if they aren‚Äôt already. Starbucks cups are a good example but there are countless others, like Coolpaste below.</p>
<p>Davies recommends making products with less packaging while Jeff Mains, CEO of the consultancy <a href="http://championleadership.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Champion Leadership Group</a>, suggests seeking out environmentally conscious suppliers, manufacturers and partners.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-eco-product-design.jpeg" alt="examples of green marketing - eco-conscious design toothpaste" width="720" height="245" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60669" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-eco-product-design.jpeg 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-eco-product-design-480x163.jpeg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.yankodesign.com/2021/02/28/the-top-10-sustainable-product-designs-that-help-you-maintain-an-eco-friendly-and-green-lifestyle/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Image source</em></a></p>
<h3>Source sustainable materials</h3>
<p>Then, think about whether you can incorporate more sustainable materials, like bamboo, cork or hemp.</p>
<p>This, said David Wurst, CEO of digital marketing agency <a href="https://www.webcitz.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Webcitz</a>, is one of the most prominent approaches to sustainable marketing.</p>
<p>‚ÄúShampoos with fewer hazardous components that dissolve more quickly in water, as well as reusable straws and water bottles, are among these items,‚Äù he added. ‚ÄúCompanies can gain traction in the green market by providing consumers with alternative items that help them feel better about their influence on the environment.‚Äù</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-ethique.png" alt="green marketing example - ethique" width="720" height="183" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60672" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-ethique.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-ethique-480x122.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://ethique.com/products/heali-kiwi-shampoo-for-dandruff-or-scalp-problems?nosto=frontpage-nosto-1-fallback-nosto-1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ethique</a> is another example of a super-sustainable brand.</em></p>
<p>Another way to ensure your items are sourced sustainably is to ensure your suppliers are ethical and provide a living wage to their employees, said David Bitton, CMO of property management firm <a href="https://www.doorloop.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DoorLoop</a>.</p>
<p>‚ÄúAdditionally, ensure that the materials used to make your products have a low environmental impact, do not contain any harmful substances and are biodegradable,‚Äù he added.<em></em></p>
<h3>Use plastic-free products and packaging</h3>
<p>Another way to do this is by going plastic-free.</p>
<p>‚ÄúToday, billions of pounds of [plastic] can be found in the swirling convergences that make up over 40% of the world&#8217;s ocean surfaces,‚Äù Wurst said. ‚ÄúThousands of seabirds, sea turtles, seals, and other marine creatures are killed each year after consuming or becoming entangled in plastic.‚Äù</p>
<p>If, for example, your packaging is single-use plastic, consider more environmentally friendly alternatives.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-zero-waste-packaging.png" alt="green marketing - plastic free packaging" width="720" height="339" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60673" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-zero-waste-packaging.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-zero-waste-packaging-480x226.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Brands like <a href="https://earthhero.com/product-category/shop-by-values/zero-waste-packaging/page/15/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Earth Hero</a> allow you to shop by specific value, like plastic-free packaging.¬†</em></p>
<p>‚ÄúWe make an effort on sustainable packaging, reducing our use of plastics and other non-compostable packaging materials by replacing them with wood, wool and straw,‚Äù said Kathryn McDavid, CEO of ecommerce company <a href="https://editorspick.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Editor&#8217;s Pick</a>.</p>
<h3>Reduce your emissions</h3>
<p>Fulfillment is another business sector that can benefit from sustainable practices.</p>
<p>‚ÄúLong-distance shipping can have a significant carbon footprint,‚Äù said Jason Ball, director of B2B agency <a href="https://consideredcontent.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Considered Content</a>. ‚ÄúTrucks and planes, among other modes of transportation, are among the major emitters of greenhouse gases.‚Äù</p>
<p>Instead, he said companies can ship in bulk to lessen their carbon impact or they can offer a green shipping option at checkout.</p>
<p>In addition, businesses can offset carbon emissions from the supply chain, Davies noted.</p>
<h3>Focus on renewable energy</h3>
<p>Beyond the products themselves, businesses can also implement eco-friendly energy practices, such as using solar, wind, hydropower or geothermal electricity.</p>
<p>‚ÄúAccess to renewable energy sources has improved in recent years and the market for harvesting renewable energy is likely to grow in the next decades as more countries invest in it,‚Äù said Jamie Opalchuk, CEO of hosting platform <a href="https://www.hostpapa.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HostPapa</a>.<img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-most-eco-friendly-brands.png" alt="most eco friendly brands that use renewable energy" width="720" height="509" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60674" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-most-eco-friendly-brands.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/green-marketing-most-eco-friendly-brands-480x339.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.visualcapitalist.com/ranked-the-50-companies-that-use-the-highest-percentage-of-green-energy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Image source</a></p>
<p>Dan Close, CEO of house-buying firm <a href="https://buyhousesinkentucky.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">We Buy Houses in Kentucky</a>, agreed, noting renewable energy can reduce production costs while also helping the environment.</p>
<h3>Assume social responsibility</h3>
<p>Finally, corporate social responsibility (CSR) allows brands to better communicate how they‚Äôre affecting positive change to conscious consumers. That‚Äôs according to Chris Gadek, vice president of growth at outdoor advertising firm <a href="https://www.adquick.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AdQuick</a>, who noted customers are often willing to pay more when a brand‚Äôs identity aligns with their beliefs.</p>
<p>‚ÄúFor this reason, businesses must embrace CSR in their brand ethos to have a competitive advantage,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúHowever, promoting your business&#8217;s CSR initiatives without tooting your own horn can be tricky. But, through a well-crafted social media campaign, you can invite customers on your brand&#8217;s journey to effect positive change in the world.‚Äù</p>
<p>You can even go as far as getting a third-party certification, such as becoming a B Corp.</p>
<p>‚ÄúCertified B Corp status is a recognizable certification that verifies your brand&#8217;s sustainability efforts and having a third party make the sustainability claims is more legitimate to consumers than the brand making the claims themselves because there&#8217;s less bias,‚Äù said Calloway Cook, president of supplement maker <a href="https://illuminatelabs.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Illuminate Labs</a>.</p>
<h2>Get your green marketing strategy in gear</h2>
<p>To recap, here are eight ways to implement green marketing:</p>
<ol>
<li>Pick the right initiative</li>
<li>Keep your efforts genuine</li>
<li>Adjust your messaging to the different levels of &#8220;green&#8221; in your audience</li>
<li>Implement eco-conscious design</li>
<li>Use plastic-free products and packaging</li>
<li>Reduce your emissions</li>
<li>Use renewable energy</li>
<li>Assume social responsibility</li>
</ol>
<p>The sooner you start, the sooner you can feel good about saving the planet. Start simple and let the story unfold from there!</p>
<p><input type="hidden" id="hippowiz-ass-injected" value="true" /><input type="hidden" id="hvmessage-toextension-listener" value="none" /></p>
